Known Problems in the Quality Control Suite.

I.
Gotchas.

Amber.
The environment variable AMBERHOME should Not be defined when preparing
input files for Dock's AMBER score, ie, during amberization.  This includes
when running the AMBER score tests.  See this FAQ for symptoms and details:
https://dock.compbio.ucsf.edu/DOCK_6/faq.htm#Error%20from%20amberize_ligand;

Python.
The Python scripts installed by Dock support both versions 2 and 3.
We have used a standard shebang, but we have reports that some macOS
platforms do not have a simple python which causes this error:
/usr/bin/env: python: No such file or directory
One way to fix this is to edit Dock's bin/*.py files and replace
#!/usr/bin/env python
with
#!/usr/bin/env python3
In the near future we may make this switch ourselves; there is a trade off
between old platforms that do not have python3 and non standard platforms.
