II.
Specific Comments on Tests.
Alphabetical by subdirectory name or test name and then by individual
file name (if any).

amber_score_181l
amber_score_1a28
amber_score_1lgu
amber_score_multiple_ligands
   Note that the environment variable AMBERHOME should be undefined
   when using AMBER score.  See this FAQ for symptoms and details:
   https://dock.compbio.ucsf.edu/DOCK_6/faq.htm#Error%20from%20amberize_ligand;

amber_score_1a28/move_everything.dockout
   The ligand energy of this test is oddly sensitive which then produces a
   significant scoring difference.  Here are values from OS Red Hat Enterprise
   Linux Server release 7.9 with gcc versions 7.3.0 and 8.4.0:
                        Amber_Score:          -50.739548
               Amber_complex_energy:        -7785.792968
                Amber_ligand_energy:          -25.431386

anchor_and_grow
bump_filter
conf_gen_int_score/dock_confgen_anchor1
contact_score
   On some platforms a different number of conformations is produced.
   If the change is small then it is usually not a sign of serious problems.
   This can cause differences in the *_scored.mol2 files.

covalent_attach_and_grow
   The tests that emit verbose growth statistics are sensitive because of
   the detailed output on the layers, segments, pruning, and clustering.

de_novo
   The tests that emit growth layering statistics are sensitive because of
   the detailed output on the root size information.

de_novo/dn_de_novo_rand
   This test is particularly sensitive because small scoring differences
   can affect the number of fragments.  This can cause differences in the
   denovo_build.mol2 file.  If the changes are small then it is usually not a
   sign of serious problems.

delphi_grid_generation
   This target is invoked by test subdirectory names chemgrid_generation and
   solvgrid_generation.
   On some platforms and with some versions of delphi the output contains
   something like this:
 igrid  mgrid          65          65
 scale oldmid igrid  0.241482      0.884000       24.6845       23.0750
   This can cause differences in the delphi.out file.

descriptor_score/Des_FPS_footprint_scored.txt
descriptor_score/Des_FPS+DCE_footprint_scored.txt
   These tests have close contacts in some residues including ASN147 and
   consequently the vdw_ref are sensitive.

descriptor_score/Des_FMS
descriptor_score/Des_FMS+SGE
descriptor_score/Des_Hun+SGE
descriptor_score/Des_SGE
descriptor_score/Des_SGE+All
descriptor_score/Des_Tan+SGE
   These tests are particularly sensitive with respect to the number of
   conformations which then produces significant scoring differences.

genetic/elitism.GA_max
   The Offspring Ensemble in this test is sensitive and can lead to a cascade
   of output differences.  However, the scoring differences at the tail of the
   output, while significant, are moderate.

minimization
   On macOS these tests are prone to insignificant but noisy differences
   in floating point numbers.  Reported platforms are OS X 10.8, 10.9.5, and
   10.12.14 using various gcc's including 4.7.4 (from Macports) and 6.3.
